# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Reverse .gitignore — allowlist-style
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Everything is ignored by default. A file enters the repository only when
# its path is explicitly un-ignored with `!` below. To add a new tracked
# path, add the corresponding `!` rule here first.
#
# Project layout:
#
#   AutoChecker/
#   ├── .gitignore                      ← this file (tracked)
#   ├── LICENSE                         ← MIT license (tracked)
#   ├── README.md                       ← usage + install docs (tracked)
#   ├── pyproject.toml                  ← build + runtime deps (tracked)
#   └── src/
#       └── autochecker/
#           └── __init__.py             ← entire CLI, REPL, Codex wrapper
#
# Deliberately NOT tracked:
#
#   .venv/                                 local Python environment
#   __pycache__/   *.pyc                   Python bytecode
#   build/   *.egg-info/                   setuptools / pipx build artifacts
#   .DS_Store                              macOS Finder metadata
#   .idea/                                 JetBrains IDE config (per-machine)
#   *.xlsx                                 student rosters — personal data
#   any grading directory                  student submissions — personal data
#
# Rationale: grading dirs contain handwritten scans with student names/work
# and the roster spreadsheet contains personal data. Keep them local-only.


# ─── Default: deny everything at repo root ──────────────────────────────────
/*


# ─── Top-level metadata we track ────────────────────────────────────────────
!/.gitignore
!/LICENSE
!/README.md
!/pyproject.toml


# ─── Python source tree ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Allow the src/ → src/autochecker/ → *.py path, re-ignore build artifacts.
!/src
/src/*
!/src/autochecker
/src/autochecker/**
!/src/autochecker/**/*.py
/src/autochecker/**/__pycache__
/src/autochecker/**/*.egg-info
